    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Medical information gets cheap</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Information about our bodies has been rapidly getting cheaper. I have been uploading my weight and body fat percentage to the Internet daily with a <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Withings-WS-50-Smart-Analyzer-Black/dp/B00BKRQ4E8/?tag=elidourado-20" target="_self">Withings scale</a> for years. My iPhone 6 tracks the number of steps I take. I occasionally record my blood pressure and heart rate on my phone. None of this is groundbreaking medical data, but it is nevertheless easier to track than ever before.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
